text: Nassarius biendongensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae, the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks. ==Description== The length of the shell varies between 9.7 mm and 14.5 mm. ==Distribution== This species occurs in the South China Sea. ==References== * Bouchet, P.; Fontaine, B. (2009). List of new marine species described between 2002–2006. Census of Marine Life. Category:Nassariidae Category:Gastropods described in 2003
title: Nassarius biendongensis
